# Vitest (unit / integration)

Use **Vitest** for business logic that does not need a browser. Use **Playwright** (`e2e-testing.mdc`) for user-facing flows.

## When Vitest is required

Add or extend Vitest when the change includes any of:

- Zod schemas and validation rules
- Pure utilities (redirect safety, scoring helpers, formatting)
- `service.ts` workflows and business rules
- Permission helpers that can run without Next.js request context (with mocks when needed)

## When Vitest is not required

Skip unit tests (note N/A in breakdown) when the change is:

- UI-only with no new logic
- Migrations or RLS with no TS business rules
- Copy or styling

If unsure, prefer one focused test file colocated with the module over skipping.

## Layout

```
features/{module}/
  schema.ts
  schema.test.ts
  utils.ts
  utils.test.ts
  service.ts
  service.test.ts
vitest.config.ts
```

- Colocate tests as `{name}.test.ts` next to the source file
- Do **not** put Vitest files under `e2e/` — that folder is Playwright only

## Conventions

- Import from `vitest`: `describe`, `it`, `expect`, `vi`
- Arrange-Act-Assert structure
- Mock Supabase and external I/O in service tests

## Running tests

```bash
npm run test
npm run test:run
npm run test:e2e
```
